    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect errno usage in socket functions\n\n### Summary\nThe socket functions in the NAS module were checking errno without first verifying that the system calls had actually failed. This led to incorrect error handling when intervening function calls overwrote errno before it was checked.\n\nSpecifically, in `socket_recv()` and `socket_send()`, the code was checking `errno == EINTR` after calling `recvfrom()`/`sendto()`, but there were intervening assignments that could overwrite errno before the check. This could cause the functions to incorrectly handle EINTR conditions or miss actual errors.\n\nThe fix ensures that errno is only checked immediately after verifying that a system call has failed (returned -1), which prevents issues where intervening function calls might overwrite errno before it's checked.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/UTIL/socket.c`: \n  - Modified `socket_recv()` to first check if `rbytes < 0` before checking `errno`\n  - Modified `socket_send()` to first check if `sbytes < 0` before checking `errno`\n  - Restructured error handling logic to properly handle EINTR and other error conditions\n\n"
}